Mount Dalrymple is a mountain in the Clarke Range, part of the Great Dividing Range, located in Central Queensland, Australia. The mountain has an elevation of  . It is amongst the higher peaks in Queensland and is located  northwest of Brisbane, and  west of . The peak and surrounding ranges are covered in dense tropical rainforest and forms part of the Eungella National Park.
It was named after George Elphinstone Dalrymple, an early European explorer of north Queensland.
